data.title: Circle and Galaxy are the only profitable crypto IPOs of 2025, rising 63% on Nasdaq, while eToro sinks 40% since debut.
data.description: The cryptocurrency Initial Public Offering (IPO) trend in 2025 has brought a reality check for investors. Among the major crypto listings, Circle Internet Financial (NYSE: CRCL) and Galaxy Digital (NASDAQ: GLXY) stand out as successful exceptions, with both companies seeing a 63% increase in their stock prices since their Nasdaq debut. In contrast, companies like eToro (NASDAQ: ETOR) are experiencing the challenges of maintaining market enthusiasm once performance comes into focus. Of the five notable cryptocurrency listings in 2025 - Circle, Galaxy Digital, eToro, Bullish (NYSE: BLSH), and Gemini (NASDAQ: GEMI) - only Circle and Galaxy have managed to sustain or surpass their initial stock prices post-IPO, according to Protos. Galaxy Digital's U.S. listing, conducted as a secondary offering rather than a traditional IPO, signifies its successful integration into American markets after years of trading on the TSE. On the other hand, Circle briefly tripled from its debut level before experiencing a slight decline. For more details, refer to the full article on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Apple (AAPL) Q4 earnings forecast at $1.77/share with revenue of $102.17 billion. Analysts raise price target to $320. Yield 0.39%.
data.description: Apple Inc. (AAPL) is set to announce its fourth-quarter earnings, with analysts predicting earnings of $1.77 per share, a significant increase from 97 cents per share a year ago. Revenue estimates stand at $102.17 billion compared to $94.93 billion last year. B of A Securities analyst Wamsi Mohan reaffirmed Apple as a Buy, increasing the price target from $270 to $320. The tech giant currently offers an annual dividend yield of 0.39%, equivalent to a quarterly dividend of 26 cents per share ($1.04 annually). Investors are intrigued by potential gains from dividends amid the recent buzz surrounding Apple's performance.

data.title: Europe's Buy Now Pay Later market to reach $293.7 billion by 2030. Market expected to grow by 12.4% annually, reaching $191.3 billion by 2025. Klarna, Afterpay, and PayPal are dominant. Local providers like Scalapay and Alma support.
data.description: A recent report on the Europe Buy Now Pay Later (BNPL) market has been released, now available on ResearchAndMarkets.com. The BNPL payment sector in Europe is projected to expand by 12.4% annually, reaching a total of US$191.3 billion by 2025. Between 2021 and 2024, the market in the region saw strong growth, with a Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR) of 2%. The report includes over 75 key performance indicators (KPIs) covering BNPL market size, end-use sectors, market share, product analysis, business model, and demographics.

data.title: Catholic Charities USA starts fundraiser to help those losing food assistance; Millions set to lose access, urgent support needed.
data.description: In Alexandria, Virginia, on October 30, 2025, it was reported that several million Americans are facing the imminent loss of access to federal food assistance programs. In response, Catholic Charities USA (CCUSA) has initiated an urgent fundraising campaign to provide food supplies to Catholic Charities agencies nationwide. This move comes as a significant number of individuals are at risk of losing vital food support, highlighting the need for immediate action.

data.title: DEMIRE expects sales opportunities next year, no early bond repayment.
data.description: DEMIRE anticipates potential for increased sales in the upcoming year, with no plans for early partial repayment of the bond by year-end. The company's sales projections indicate a promising outlook for growth, positioning DEMIRE for continued success moving forward.

data.title: Miami-based startup Flamingo launches OpenFrame platform, attracting 1,000 MSPs on waitlist (3% market share) and 150 early adopters.
data.description: A startup in Miami, Flamingo, has emerged from stealth mode unveiling their OpenFrame platform, which merges AI automation with open-source infrastructure. This platform aims to revolutionize the business model for managed service providers (MSPs) - entities offering IT support to small and medium-sized enterprises. Prior to the official launch, over 1,000 MSPs have signed up on Flamingo's waitlist, accounting for about 3% of the market. Additionally, there are over 150 early adopters currently in the active testing phase of the platform.

data.title: Atlanta Community Food Bank launches $5M Crisis Response Plan due to government shutdown, amid 70% increase in food recipients.
data.description: The Atlanta Community Food Bank revealed plans to implement a Crisis Response Plan to assist partner organizations and those facing food insecurity in the metro Atlanta and north Georgia regions. This move is in reaction to the federal government shutdown, which has compounded the demand for food assistance at a critical time. The Food Bank is currently aiding 70% more individuals each month compared to before, emphasizing the pressing need for continued support during this challenging period.

data.title: Agilysys wins 2025 HTNG TechOvation Award for Book with S.P.E.N.D. tech, revolutionizing hospitality industry with innovative booking system.
data.description: Agilysys, a prominent global provider of advanced hospitality software and services, revealed that its Book with S.P.E.N.D. technology has won the 2025 HTNG TechOvation Award. This distinction is highly regarded in the hospitality sector for technological innovations. The cutting-edge booking technology offers a new approach to online package bookings in the industry. Agilysys, listed under Nasdaq as AGYS, continues to lead with innovative solutions in hospitality.

data.title: NETSCOUT enhances Kubernetes container visibility to address complex cloud needs, including AIOps, cybersecurity. 165 characters.
data.description: NETSCOUT® SYSTEMS, INC., a prominent company traded on NASDAQ under NTCT, unveiled a new solution in Westford, Mass. The innovation targets the rising demand for enhanced observability in intricate cloud environments among organizations. As the use of extensive, multi-cluster Kubernetes deployments continues to surge, businesses encounter obstacles in maintaining visibility and addressing blind spots in their settings. This announcement reflects the company's commitment to meeting these challenges head-on by providing comprehensive observability, AI Operations (AIOps), cybersecurity, and defense against Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks.

data.title: Wolters Kluwer ranks #11 globally in Chartis RiskTech100 2026 report for a 4th consecutive year, excelling in Regulatory Intelligence and Liquidity Risk capabilities.
data.description: In New York, Wolters Kluwer, known for professional information and software solutions, has achieved the prestigious #11 global ranking by Chartis Research in their latest Chartis RiskTech100 2026 report. The company was recognized as a Category Leader for Regulatory Intelligence for the fourth consecutive year and for Liquidity Risk capabilities for the second year in a row. This marks their ongoing excellence in these areas. Wolters Kluwer continues to prove itself as a top expert solutions provider in the industry.
